  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support community impacted by Covid in 5 districts of MP</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Overall intervention to benefit 1600 Covid impacted HH, migrants, single women headed, PWD and household without earnings.  Providing nutri mix food to children help them to recover severe malnutrition.  Setting up Covid WASH stations and surveillance help in containment of disease and to maintain hygiene among the community.  Linkages between hospitals and PRI to benefit the community.  150 volunteers to work within the community help to monitor the Covid spread and to conduct awareness on covid related behaviour and vaccination.  Distribution of hygiene kits including masks and sanitizer help in providing protection. second phase to work on village level infrastructure and health facilities to be improved would benefit the community.  unconditional cash transfer to support in alternate livelihood or other expenses which are unavoidable.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project intervention will be in 5 districts of Madhya Pradesh. They are Sagar, Betul, Mandla, Sehore and Khandwa where the targeted community belongs to indigenous tribal community. The project to be implemented in 90 villages and 150 community volunteers to work as front line warriors.  Activity includes a) capacity building of volunteers and community on covid appropriate behaviour and vaccination b) installation of community wash stations per village c) distribution of dry ration to 1600 beneficiaries d) hygiene kits including sanitary pads to 2000 beneficiaries e) vulnerable HH to be identified through rapid survey f) establishing linkage with hospitals, PRIs and health professional to support community access to treatment. In the second phase CASA to cover 4 districts and 60 villages. The intervention to cover support in rural health infrastructure, unconditional cash transfer, supply of hygiene kits to women &amp; girls and dry ration support to 1200 HH.</narrative>
  </description>
